    "updated_at": "2016-07-06T09:44:39Z",
    "body": "I am receiving the same bug, however, when I make a call to set the maximum size, the minimum size is unset, and when I set the minimum size, the maximum size is unset. I have logged the results of the following code:\n\n```\nmainWindow.setMinimumSize(320, 320);\nconsole.log(mainWindow.getMinimumSize());\nconsole.log(mainWindow.getMaximumSize());\n\nmainWindow.setMaximumSize(1280, 768);\nconsole.log(mainWindow.getMinimumSize());\nconsole.log(mainWindow.getMaximumSize());\n```\n\nThis produces the following output:\n\n```\n[ 320, 320 ]\n[ 0, 0 ]\n[ 0, 0 ]\n[ 1280, 768 ]\n```\n\nUsing the workaround stated above to set the maximum window size after a timeout results in the same output.\n"
